{# ── SUMMARY · real H2 carrying the short-version prose (right after the in-brief). Speakable schema anchor #ny-svc-speak-summary preserved. (H2: The short version.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="ny-svc-speak-summary" style="padding-top:8px;">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="ph"><span class="ph__t">In short</span><span class="ph__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:18px;">The short version.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      {%- for p in summary %}<p>{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── WHO + SPLIT · who should talk to a ProAdvisor vs. who Intuit should handle (incl-card + checklist). Sheet-7 intent-split, ABOVE the funnel content; the Intuit card routes account/billing/login intent AWAY to Intuit. (H2: Is a ProAdvisor call the right call?) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="ny-svc-speak-split" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="ph"><span class="ph__t">Who should call &mdash; and who Intuit should handle</span><span class="ph__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:14px;">Is a ProAdvisor call the right call?</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 32px;max-width:62ch;">A discovery call with this team is about <strong>your own books</strong> &mdash; how your QuickBooks file is set up and run. It is not Intuit support. The split below tells you where to go.</p>
    <div class="r-2">
      {%- for s in split %}
      <div class="incl-card">
        <p class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:10px;">{{ s.tag | safe }}</p>
        <h3>{{ s.title | safe }}</h3>
        <p style="font-size:14.5px;line-height:1.6;color:var(--color-ink-mute);margin:10px 0 0;">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
        <ul class="checklist">{%- for li in s.list %}<li>{{ li | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}</ul>
        {%- if s.cta %}<p style="margin:16px 0 0;"><a href="{{ s.href }}"{% if s.rel %} rel="{{ s.rel }}"{% endif %} style="font-size:14px;font-weight:600;color:var(--color-accent);">{{ s.cta | safe }}</a></p>{%- endif %}
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="prose" style="margin-top:24px;">{{ splitNote | safe }}</p>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── CONVERSATION · how the call runs (process-grid, 3 steps). 3 frozen H3s verbatim. (H2: A real conversation, not a sales funnel. + 3 H3s) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="ny-svc-speak-conversation">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="ph"><span class="ph__t">What to expect on the call</span><span class="ph__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:14px;">A real conversation, not a sales funnel.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 36px;max-width:62ch;">You speak with a Certified ProAdvisor &mdash; the kind of person who would do or oversee the work &mdash; not a salesperson and not a product-support queue. Here is how it goes.</p>
    <div class="process-grid">
      {%- for c in conversation %}
      <div class="process-step">
        <span class="process-step__n">{{ c.num | safe }}</span>
        <h3>{{ c.title | safe }}</h3>
        <p>{{ c.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── COVERS vs NOT · what the call covers and what it is NOT (Intuit support) (incl-card + checklist). Sheet-7 boundary restated explicitly; the second card routes Intuit intent AWAY. (H2: What the call covers — and what it does not.) ── #}
